rComments: I had him in 2012 and he is hands down my favourite prof that I ever had. He was like my grandpa who also passed away.. I think people who weren't successful in his course either skipped classes, didn't do the readings and actually study and/or had a very poor attitude toward him. He made me consider becoming an anthropologist! He was a good man.
RIP- He was an incredibly dedicated educator. He will be sorely missed. Thanks for helping me get to where I am today.
It was his last year of teaching.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Baker is absolutely amazing! Great sense of humor, grading is a bit tough, but show up to every class and do ALL readings, yes there is a lot but do ALL of them to get a good grade. His explanations are clear, lot's of examples and easy to take notes as he speaks. I'm in 3rd year and he's the best prof I've ever had.

go to class and take notes and it's an easy grade! very clear about what will be on the exam and knows what he's talking about when he lectures. kind of monotone so it's easy to zone out but if you really pay attention you're good to go

No, he doesn't use email or blackboard but his class was my favourite. Content is interesting, he gets right to the point in his lectures and is easy to understand. If you pay attention to what he says and take notes  you'll get a good mark. He's also really funny at times which is unexpected. Glad I have him again next semester!

I heard a lot of people complaining about taking Baker's class, so I wanted to clear things up. He does use a projector in class but it's because of this that the class is so easy. As long as you show up to class, take good notes and pay attention you will have not trouble earning an A. He tells you everything that will be on the final as well!

John Baker is a good Prof. His lectures are easy to understand  and his expectations are clear. He marks the midterms and is really fair. However his TAs are extremely hard markers and  can often talk down to the students making them feel like idiots.

EVERYTHING in his course has to do with what he SAYS during his lectures. If you're an auditory learner, then this is for you. Me and the majority of other students? Not so much. Tests are hard, even harder marker. If you miss one class, you miss a lot. Doesn't use email, no way to contact. Went to his office hours and he was extremely unhelpful.

I love Baker, my favorite prof this semester by far, he sits down for his lectures and uses a projector but he gives lots of time to copy notes, his tests and assignments are easy. If you ask him to clarify he will, he is straight up and has no filter which I think makes him real. I find him really funny at times, ppl say hes monotone yesno
what he will be testing are all in his note. need to be focused during lectures, better have all the note

The man literally told me to drop his class and that I wouldn't pass just cause Id skipped the first 5 classes apparently it was impossible for me to  pass the test that was like a week and a bit away lol... like really  I found all of his lecture notes online and bought the textbook and passed the test pretty easily. It was also only worth 10

Honestly one of my favourite profs ever. He doesn't use email or virtual campus at all...so you have to go to class to take notes, but it's so worth it. Really interesting lectures and he's funny. One of the best profs.
not bad. quizes and assignments kind of easy straightforward. everything he say is used in the tests. only uses overhead projector and no emails. takes up quizes right away.

AVOID THIS MAN LIKE THE PLAGUE. He refuses to use any kind of technology and writes his notes by hand. He tends to scribble off some of the words he writes, which makes it somewhat confusing. He's an AWESOME guy, but seriously, his class was tough. He's a really harsh grader as well. Oh, and don't try sending him emails; he completely ignores them.

Best prof at uOttawa, I have taken a number of his classes. Go to every single lecture and study your notes, easy A+. The class averages are so low because students skip and try to rely on the readings. He is very fair but unsympathetic if you skip.

I honestly love this prof one of the best I have had. extremely helpful. some people find him dry but he has this dry monotone humour that is actually pretty funny. EVERYTHING is on overheads (only study these and you will do great!). As long as you study the notes you will do well. Really really nice too
I have had him for 1101, 2111, 2112 and hopefully many more. He is awesome however he is getting older and sick, I hope he gets healthier because he is an amazing prof.

Class is mandatory because he talks the whole time. Readings are also mandatory for quizzes. The quizzes are decent, should not be hard especially when he explains extremely well and is clear on what he is explaining. He doesn't go off topic and only talks about what he writes on the board.

Attendance isn't mandatory but make sure to go to his classes- he uses many helpful examples. Very eager to help and elaborate inside and outside of the class. He breaks down and explains the material so well that with the aid of the assigned text book it's impossible to get a bad grade in his class. :) Also, a great sense of humour. ;)

Really nice person but the course material is quite dry. The assignments were very easy and easily graded but the exams were definitely not easy. Within his exams he uses a lot of examples so when studying it may be a good idea to make some examples to correspond with each term for yourself.

At first I was annoyed by the projector, but it's easy to follow and makes you show up to class because nothing is posted on virtual campus. An easy A if you study what he tells you to study, copy his projector notes, and do some readings. Overall a funny guy with a really dry sense of humour. Loved him!

Go to class, copy the slides, and you've got an easy A. Baker is really nice but also really boring and not particularly clear. Rather than a midterm or paper worth a lot, there are lots of little quizzes and two papers, which is time-consuming and annoying. If you have problems understanding something, use the textbook or Wikipedia.
His exams are easy if you study the material and make sure to do the readings. Monotone as hell and is a fan of going off topic/rambling.

Baker speaks monotonely because he was born with the inability to speak at all, the only way he was able to learn to speak was exactly the way he was taught (monotone) his slides are sufficient enough to do well on his tests.
Excellent prof that is very clear in his lectures. Doesn't use Virtual Campus so class attendance is a must.  Pleasant demeanor. One of my favorite classes.
Likes giving midterms the day after holidays. How considerate :/

Came to class for Sociology. Instead paid to listen to him go on in monotone about prostitutes, evolution, his rebel brother, his 'saggy butt', and other unrelated things. His readings were all about prostitution and biker women. He got frustrated when I asked for advice on my term paper, and the tests had little to do with covered material.

The only reason Baker is doing so well on this site has to be because of the number of reported ratings. He is a terrible prof that re-reads his already irrelevant assigned readings, rambles in monotone about nonsense, & gives exams which are unrelated to course material. His class averages are very low. Avoid at all costs, or hope he retires...

Worst prof I've had at university by far. Gives long, irrelevant readings, babbles on about off-topic nonsense in class, and gives tests that have nothing to do with the course material. The lowest grade I have gotten in university and high school was a C+. I failed John Baker's class, as did many others. Avoid at all costs, if you can.
Lectures are crystal clear. TAs however were less than helpful. Not a fan of the various multiple choice tests throughout the term.

An overall good guy. I loved his in class stories, they never failed to make the whole class laugh! The tests were hard, as they were worth 10% for 10 questions (worth 1 point each). Content wasn't too difficult, but I didn't' read a lot of the course pack, just took really detailed lecture nots and I am sitting at a 93 :)

I love John Baker, he has a dry sense of humor which I enjoyed. He is old school, but he took the time to hand write notes for students to take down. His midterms were really easy, and the exam was relevant.This course influenced me to minor in sociology.I definitely recommend taking his class. Go to class,copy the notes and do well.
hard to understand, speaks monotone, and the the note i find to be all over the place and refers to previous note way to often
Excellent Professor. Some people may find him monotone, but I find him funny, clear and always gives good examples which perfectly outline whatever he is teaching

Baker is a great prof. Funny and used good examples. Midterms were short and simple. There was only one short assignment and the final was completely relevant to what we learned. I recommend taking this class, easy A!

The next three comments under me are EXACTLY how I feel. His quizzes were so unfair and his lectures were SOOO boring. I could NOT handle that class. I tried so hard and still barely passed that class. How did he get so many good comments??

The most monotone and uninteresting teacher at U of O. Impossible to understand, examinations completely irrelevant to the course and have I mentionned boring? Class average was very low... RUN! RUN! RUN!

Lectures were boring as he has a monotone voice but he explains things very clearly. Quizzes were hard; didn't need to know many details but with only 10 questions it was easy to miss a few and do poorly. Overall an okay prof if you study for the quizzes and can stay awake to take notes on his overheads.

I can't believe all the great feedback this guy got. Maybe he has changed, everyone I knew in this class did not enjoy this prof. He was very intelligent but his lectures were SO SO boring.Quizzes were hard, class average was 40%.I would never take this again in a million years

John Baker is a really intelligent professor, which is awesome if you actually want to learn something:D! He gives lots of examples so it is pretty hard to get lost.  I really like this prof and this class, highly recommended:D

Great Prof!  Go to lectures and take good notes, readings aren't really necessary because he mentions them in class anyways.  Tests and exams are predictable and straightforward.  Probably the only class I was excited to go to on a monday morning at 8:30.  Take his class!!

To be blunt, Dr. Baker is amazing. His lectures were worth the 0830 start-up, and his readings were interesting and informative. What more, Dr. Baker is flexible with tests, a fair marker, and a genuinely quirky fellow. Word of advice: don't skip. You're missing out on a good time, and you're shooting yourself in the foot. Highly recommended.

This professor made me interested in sociology --- A subject I never enjoyed before. After attending his lectures I felt less ignorant about my knowledge of society in general. He is funny and kind. Also, he tries to make the material interesting for the students. Remember to take good notes and listen!

Professor is one of the best professors that a student can meet. He is honest, he teaches everything without bias (and presents all sides), and fully knows his material. If the University of Ottawa had some integrity they would make him a tenured. Go to lectures and write the simple points he writes down and you will learn and get a good mark.

I`ve had this teacher for 3 courses now, and I have to say hes the best prof that I've had in University so far. He knows his stuff really well and gives many examples that make his lecture easy to undertand.He is also very approchable. The only thing is that he does not posts his notes on virtual campus so attendance is a must.
Old SKOOL.  Uses overheads and doesn't post notes.  Make sure you attend every class, but pretty simple

Such a great man! Knows a lot about what he is talking about. And while his lectures can sometimes be boring... he often throws in an unexpected joke or 2 that lightens the mood in the classroom! Go to class to get the notes (they are very important)... and study... Pretty easy A in this one!

Such a good prof... he really emphasizes all the important concepts you need to know for upcoming tests and what not. He is a very sweet man and loves what he is teaching. I feel sometimes as though he is a portable library, very smart person! Dont miss class though, he puts up great slides you dont want to miss for upcoming tests
a nice little old man, and his notes are perfect. you can get an A easily, just go to class and study the day before the quizes and exam. GREAT PROF!

He's the kind of Professor that makes you glad you did the post-secondary thing (there aren't many of 'em).  His lecture's are fascinating and he seems to be genuinely interested in the material he's teaching as well as in his student's development.  A really great class and an unrivalled Prof!
Really sweet, has the greatest stories and manner of telling them, you forget you're in class. Easy quizes, its pretty cute when he thinks he's made them hard. most captivating class i've taken
he's so cute! really clear and really nice! i would definately take his class again!

GREAT PROF! one of the best profs i've had so far. just copy down the slides and you will definitely get an A! don't bother buying the textbook, you won't need it. sometimes goes off telling stories that are so long you forget the point he is trying to make, but at least they're interesting! take this class for a relatively easy A, but go to class!
Haha this guy is pricless, he's really quirky, but he also teaches really well, make sure you actually go to class though or else you'll be screwed
Classes were a little boring, but the notes were fabulous. If you stay on top of it all you'll excel. NOT FOR AVID SKIPPERS. Very cute teacher with his quirky personality.
He's awesome. Haven't done the final yet but the midterms we're so easy I got 100% on all of them.
He's adorable!!! Trust me you learn a lot and he's so cute. The class isn't even that hard.
Had him 6 times, never disapointed. I love how he always brings tea to class, picks it up throughout the lecture and never drinks it.

He's awesome!! I loved the class! He was largely the reason why I decided to take a minor in Sociology. The class was fair and he's so cute and adorable. He's always there to help his students. The midterms and final are fair, just memorize his notes. He makes the class interesting and his assignments are not that bad. He's a really nice prof!

Great guy, knows his stuff. Puts up overhead notes every class. Just show up copy down the notes and study these notes for the midterms and exams, and you'll get an A! Dont buy the books, waste of money.
The best prof ever!  Clear, easy to understand, and just the overall best - made me want to do an MA!
He's so nice and the lectures are really interesting. I would definitely recommend him.
Fantastic prof. If you have the chance take any course with him.

LOVE HIM SO MUCH! take his class in the summer, that way he dismisses you early to let out his dog! hehe. Memorize his overhead notes and skim the readings (MC questions on those) and his final exam is easy if you study the basics. All in all, great prof and his lectures are very interesting! they keep you wanting more
He is adorable!!! Love!!!

I've taken 4 of his classes and was about to take the fifth but the sociology quantitative research methods is not equivalent to the psychology one. The psych's is stronger. If you can take a course with Baker, TAKE IT! Unless you plan on missing classes and don't have anyone to take the notes from. Then you're just screwed!

BAKER IS INCREDIBLE! He has overheads in class. If you show up to class copy the overheads and study them you should be fine. The three tests he gives are EASY! Multiple choice with some short answer questions. He makes notes of the Text book during class; That's probably all that's needed from the text book. He's approachable and ALWAYS SMILING!
he's boring, but hes really nice, and his marking schemes are easy. he's a good professor unlike edith smith, shes the devil in disguise

He definetly knows his stuff but tends to go on tangents and focus solely on the sociology of the workplace. His TA's are  not on the same page when it comes to marking (one is WAY easier than the other) but other than that it was an okay class.  Sometimes i just wanted to give him a hug when the class was being disrespectful and talking over him.

He is one of the best profs ever. You just have to pay attention during the class and you can get an A-. But beware most of his TA(s) are really useless and I would suggest if you have questions, go talk to Baker.

DO NOT TAKE A COURSE WITH THIS PROF.  BEWARE- he is very hard and does not care about your grade.  THe final exams are worth 50% of your grade while 25% is allocated to an essay worth 25% and 3 tests that are 25% in total.  He does not give out high marks and when one gets a bad grade on a essay he blames it on the fact that you are a bad writer.
funniest guy you'll ever encounter as a prof... pure comedic genious cute old man who loves to hold a coffee cup and not drink it
Sometimes got off topic. Conveys material really well.
Honestly, he is the most boring/monotone prof in the world. His lectures are brutally boring and if you dont pay attention then your mark will suffer its a lose/lose situation.
Excellent Prof and a nice guy. You definitely have to take a course taught by him if you wish to get an A.

He is a really good prof and a nice guy. All you need to do is show up to lectures, copy his overhead notes and study those notes as much as you can before the exam. He repeats important material often with somewhat interesting analogies and example which make them hard to forget come exam time.
Great Prof!
Dont bother buying the textbook, cause you dont actually read all the articles so just photocopy them. He is an awesome teacher and he explains very well.

do yourself a favour and take his class before you graduate. very easy, great anecdotes, sort of a cute bumbly prof. he seems so forlorn though! contrary to what another person said, i do not see any discrimination problem, but the way he explains certain topics might seem discriminatory if you take it the wrong way. i think he's very open-minded!!

AWESOME PROF!! Hillarious man, very sweet. He's so cute it's ridiculous. His classes are interesting, and you can tell he's there for the students. He wants us to enjoy what we're learning and he does a great job! Tests and assignments are pretty easy, and him and TA's are very fair with their marking! TAKE HIS CLASS!!

Has a loud voice that really projects across the auditorium. Could really see that he had a great deal of experience in teaching.. knows how to get the students attention and classes are always interesting and informative. He's really funny at times and the quizzes/tests are super easy. Take a class with him and you'll learn lots!

Baker should retire. I've noticed that he has a discrimination problem and thats very unfortunate considering the major part of this class discussed how scientists should be objective and not be biased or influenced by their subjectivity. I'm serious!

excellent class! he managed to make even the most mundane theories fascinating! absolutely hilarious and down to earth. very friendly and approachable. his notes are clear and interesting. going to lectures was a pleasure, i never dreaded going to class! it's a shame not more professors taught like him! way to go, baker!

Cutest man alive!Always smiling!Such a great prof! Attending class & taking the notes crucial-but mid-terms are super easy and he is VERy clear in what you need to know. Very helpful! AMAZING PROF! (voice monotonous at times but funny anecdotes keep you listening!)

Baker is an amazing prof!  he knows what hes talking about and has helpful overheads. his tests are super-simple, but you really have to attend class to do well.  overall, hes a sweet man and a great prof

What a turtle! He's the Cutest little man I've ever seen. I think he lives off caffine- I've never seen him without his huge coffee in his hand. And don't even get me started on those overhead notes

His classes are boring but straight forward, I found his T.A's to be extremely helpful so I did well on essays because they pretty much told you exaclty what to write. If you can sit through the lectures you should be fine.

I also took SOC1102 with him, as well as SOC2305. He is a great prof! Honestly, wish that everyone had the same teaching methods as him... Took a boring class and made me get through it. His notes are really good and make the readings much easier...If you know your notes, you will do extremely well on the test and the exam!
his overheads were really helpful and his stories were funny at times. the only thing to remember is the midterms are only easy if you study your class notes well.
he is a average prof. he provides good notes. however every time he says objective it pisses me off. he needs to work on that word and he will be a great prof.
Going to class was like storytime... very enjoyable but the tests were not so easy, as I recall.

Cutie Patooty! Baker, I miss you. Other sociology profs don't hold a candle. He's found a tried and true teaching method that's helpful, clear, and as interesting as possible under the circumstances. Love it. Love him. Baker, you are gold.

This was my best prof, he knew what he was talking about all of the time and had such an incredible amount of knowledge on all of the course materials. His anecdotes and stories that accompanied the notes made everything easy to understand. Very cute man who would always have on an adorable smile!
this class is so easy, all the notes are on overheads.  just make sure to study.
overall, he's a very good professor. He's interesting and knows his stuff.

Very good first year class! Baker really knows how to teach.  I was amazed that structured profs really did exist.  With notes on overheads and interesting anecdotes and readings, it's really worth it to attend class! Can't forget the tea cup and the nice big warm smile on his face! Best Prof so far
He was very clean and his tests were straight forward
Excellent Prof.  Knows the materail really well.  The tests that are given help a great deal for the final exam.
I think he is a cool prof who looks like a turtle!

Great Prof, ya its true he is monotone and its hard to stay awake in his class but he makes it easy for you to do well by putting the notes up on overhead for you to copy down and the only things u need for the tests are those notes! Has a good sense of humor and great intelligence too!

My absolute fav professor of all time! If you don't appreciate dry wit then you won't find him funny. However, if you like having a professor that is interesting, makes the material easy to understand while teaching you new (or old) concepts that you will actually grasp, he is for you!
He's a little cutie patootie. Maybe boring, but you always know where you stand in his class, and he actually TRIES to help you do well. The 3 midterms are easy, and good study tools.
VERY monotone, but some of the topics are actually interesting, but he's really biased against the United States?! :S

lectures may be fairly difficult to get through because he is very monotone. however if you are really interested in the class it shouldn't be a problem. he knows his subject through. make sure to take notes

Best. Professor. Ever. Puts more effort into teaching than anyone else I've ever had. Yes, he repeats what he says, because he knows we tend to drift off by nature. But this way you learn most of the lecture in class.Also, he's really funny/great examples

Very clear, very organized, very helpful, very nice!  Material is easy to follow and understand, and prof makes every effort to communicate clearly and ensure that students understand completely.
